task_text:
CALLING ALL DATA ENTRY PROFESSIONALS - APPLY NOW!!! If you are an Entry-Level professional looking for a fully-remote position with a great Non-profit Organization, Apply today! Position Summary: The Data Management Coordinator I will work as a member of the Data Management department to maintain our database of registrant records, to ensure that all eligible registrants are placed on the national registry in as timely a manner as possible, and to increase aggregate registrant availability at the Confirmatory Typing level by updating registrant data, responding to (aspirant) registrant correspondence, and performing registrant outreach. S/He will work closely with the Data Management Manager and fellow Data Management Coordinators I/II/III to learn in full what the Data Management department's responsibilities are, how the department's specific responsibilities fit into the overall mission, and how to successfully perform therm.

Responsibilities include (but are not limited to):
Updating registrants' personally identifying information (PII) in the database,
Attending to registrant/public requests and inquiries by telephone and email;
Printing and distributing correspondence to prospective, current, and former registrants;
Following up on unreturned kit-by-mail registrations and processing intradepartmental undelivered mail;
Processing registrant registration forms through to the data entry company;
Importing all registrant data/records;
Attending to the registrant to-do's regularly;
Coordinating with external vendors to the fulfillment of the kit-by-mail registrations;
Participating in intra- and interdepartmental meetings, projects, and ad hoc duties
